						               													<description>PopSavvy is a game that challenges each player's social awareness. It is played by a couple sharing a bottle of wine, by friends and family groups at a dinner table, by classrooms of kids getting to know each other, and by pub crowds demonstrating their social savvy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players win the game by being the best at predicting how individuals or groups of people will answer thought-provoking, fun, and/or revealing YES/NO questions. The goal is to &amp;quot;know the crowd&amp;quot; better than your opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay is very simple. A player selects a PopSavvy card and chooses one question from five categories - SELF, LIFE, lOVE, HOME, or WORLD. Eg. &amp;quot;Does drunkenness reveal the true character of a person&amp;quot;? Each player votes YES or NO on a scoresheet, predicts how many players will vote YES, discovers how many actually voted YES, and earns a score based on how accurate their prediction was. After several questions, the most socially savvy person will reveal themselves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
